**Overall Meaning:**

"Freed from all sins, one would obtain perfect knowledge. The mind becomes swift, and gray hair (and other signs of aging) disappear." 

**Note:** This verse describes some of the benefits of practicing pranayama and cultivating inner purity.  It suggests that by freeing oneself from negative tendencies and attaining knowledge, one can experience a rejuvenation of body and mind. 
